  "text": "The splicing attack is one type of tampering in which different regions of the same or separate sources are combined to create a new fake image. In [CITATION_1] , Riess et al. introduced a method for detecting image splicing through the change of illumination environment of the spliced object. They could overcome one of the biggest challenges which is computing the lighting environment from homogeneous materials. Their approach could successfully improve the mean error by almost 30%. Yet, hair, structurally unsmooth regions, and highly textured clothes were from the model limitations.",
